Description: Limestone ostracon: on the recto seven incomplete lines (washed off on the right) of a text containing a part of a hymn. On the verso in two columns respectively six and four incomplete lines of a list of objects and names(?), accompanied by a small drawing of a god.
Curator's comments: = J. J. Černy and A.H. Gardiner, ‘Hieratic Ostraca’ (Oxford 1957), pl. 41.3; published by Fischer-Elfert. Bibliography: J. J. Černy and A.H. Gardiner, ‘Hieratic Ostraca’ (Oxford 1957), p. 12 and pl. XLI, 3.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136397) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136397)
